
Vibe Coding = Writing high-level natural language prompts
to generate working code using Generative AI.

Goal:
- Describe "what you want", not "how to code it"
- AI handles implementation details



Techniques used:

1. Role Prompting
2. Context Setting
3. Constraints Definition
4. Output Format Specification
5. Example-driven prompting (Few-shot)
6. Iterative refinement



PROMPT:
"You are a senior Java Spring Boot developer.
Create a REST microservice for user management with:
- GET /users/{id}
- POST /users
- Use in-memory storage
- Include exception handling
Return clean production-ready code."



GENERATED OUTPUT (AI RESULT):

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/users")
public class UserController {

    private Map<Integer, String> db = new HashMap<>();

    @GetMapping("/{id}")
    public ResponseEntity<String> getUser(@PathVariable int id) {
        if (!db.containsKey(id)) {
            throw new RuntimeException("User not found");
        }
        return ResponseEntity.ok(db.get(id));
    }

    @PostMapping
    public ResponseEntity<String> createUser(@RequestBody String user) {
        int id = db.size() + 1;
        db.put(id, user);
        return ResponseEntity.ok("User created with ID: " + id);
    }
}



EVALUATION:
✔ Correct REST structure
✔ Works for prototype
✔ Missing database layer (limitation)
✔ Good for MVP development



